                <h2>Dog Care</h2>
                <h3>Basic Care</h3>
                <p>Provide your dog with plenty of fresh water and nutritious food. Ensure your dog has a comfortable place to rest and regular exercise.</p>
                
                <h3>Grooming</h3>
                <p>Regular grooming is important to keep your dog's coat healthy and clean. Brush your dog's fur regularly and trim their nails as needed.</p>
                
                <h3>Health</h3>
                <p>Regular veterinary check-ups are essential for maintaining your dog's health. Keep up with vaccinations, flea control, and any necessary treatments.</p>
                
                <h3>Exercise and Play</h3>
                <p>Dogs need regular exercise and mental stimulation. Provide your dog with toys, walks, and interactive play sessions.</p>
                
                <h3>Affection and Socialization</h3>
                <p>Spend time with your dog and show them affection. Proper socialization is important for their emotional well-being.</p>
                
